x4freetext: THE PULSED NEUTRON GENERATOR AT
TECHNISCHE UNIVERSITAT DRESDEN. 130 KEV DEUTERON
ENERGY WITH CURRENTS OF 20 TO 30 MICROAMPS WERE USED.
ZERO-DEGREE NEUTRONS FROM THE D + D REAC-
TION WERE USED.
ZERO-DEGREE NEUTRONS FROM THE D + T REAC-
TION WERE USED.
.QUASI-MONOENERGETIC.
GAMMA COUNTERS WERE USED TO MEASURE INDUCED
ACTIVITY.
A 36 CM3 GE-LI DETECTOR WAS USED FOR THE
MONITOR FOILS IN THE D-D EXPERIMENT AND ALL THE D-T
MEASUREMENTS.
A 65 CM3 HPGE DETECTOR WAS USED FOR THE
SAMPLES IN THE D-D EXPERIMENT.
.FOR THE D-D EXPERIMENTS, AS2O3, 2.5 G, 99.5
PERCENT, AND SELENIUM, 2.5 G, 99.5 PERCENT, WERE
PRESSED INTO 1.3 CM DIAMETER X 0.5 CM THICK PELLETS.
GE02, 5 G, 99.999 PERCENT, WAS FILLED INTO
A 1.3 CM DIAM X 3.1 CM POLYETHYLENE TUBE WITH 0.05 CM
THICK WALLS. ALL SAMPLES HAD NATURAL ISOTOPIC
COMPOSITION. ALUMINIUM, IRON AND NICKEL MONITOR FOILS
WERE ATTACHED AT THE FRONT AND THE BACK OF THE
SAMPLES. THE GEO2 SAMPLES WERE COVERED WITH 1 MM
CADMIUM PLATES TO ELIMINATE THERMAL NEUTRONS.
FOR THE D-T EXPERIMENTS, AS2O3, 1 G, 99.5 PERCENT,
SELENIUM, 2.5 G, 99.5 PERCENT, AND GERMANIUM, 2.5 G,
99.99 PERCENT, WERE PRESSED INTO 0.9 OR 1.3 CM
DIAMETER X 0.5 CM THICK PELLETS. ALL
SAMPLES HAD NATURAL ISOTOPIC COMPOSITION. ALUMINIUM
MONITOR FOILS WERE ATTACHED AT THE FRONT AND THE BACK
OF THE SAMPLES. THE GERMANIUM SAMPLES WERE COVERED
WITH 1 MM CADMIUM PLATES TO ELIMINATE THERMAL NEUTRON
THE PEAK ARES WERE DETERMINED BY SIMPLE SUMMING
WITH LINEAR BACKGROUND SUBTRACTION.
FROM IRDF.
FROM IRDF. FOR LOW ENERGY
ONLY
.THE DATA WERE CORRECTED FOR INTERFERING NUCLEAR
REACTIONS. FOR THE SE-76(N,P)AS-76 AND
GE-72,73(N,P)GA-72,73 REACTIONS, CONTRIBUTIONS
FROM (N,D) + (N,NP ) + (N,PN) REACTIONS WERE SUBTRACT
FOR THE 14.7 MEV DATA ONLY, ASSUMING SUMMED CROSS SEC
TIONS OF 4.5, 4 AND 3 MB, RESP. THE CROSS SECTIONS OF
THE GE-76(N,G)GE-75 REACTION WERE CORRECTED FOR
CONTRIBUTIONS FROM THE GE-74(N,G)GE-75 REACTION USING
NEUTRON TRANSPORT CALCULATIONS.
